Incidents.Name: River Fire
Incidents.Location: Oak Grove Road and Oak Grove School Road in Mariposa County
Incidents.ConditionStatement:
Current Conditions

Today, firefighters continued to fight fire aggressively and reinforce control lines. Mopup efforts have begun and will continure throughout the evening. Damage assessment is ongoing. As damage inspection teams continue to assess the fire damage, numbers of structures affected may change. For your safety and the safety of the first responders, continue to drive safely on the roadways and adhere to posted road signs.

Evacuations: Madera County:
  • Road 800
  • Road 810
  • Road 812
  • Road 600
  • Apache Road to 612 both sides
  • Road 600 between Apache Ranch and Blazing Saddle Trail and JWP Ranch Road

    • Evacuation Warnings: Madera County:
  • Road 600
  • Road 612
  • Road 415

    • Mariposa County: Open to residents only
  • Indian Peak at Usona to Road 800
  • Oak Grove Road at Oak Grove School Road to Road 800
  • Stumpfield from Leonard to Madera County Line

    • American Red Cross:
  • New Life Christian Fellowship Church 5089 Cole Rd. Mariposa, CA
    • Road Closures: Madera County:
  • Road 600 to Road 619
  • Road 600 to Road 612
  • Road 800 to Road 613

    • Mariposa County:
  • Oak Grove Road at Oak Grove School Road.
  • Oak Grove Road at Road 800

    • Animal Evacuations information:
  • Madera County – 559-675-7769
  • Mariposa County – 209-966-3615
